ks of Kant, Fichte, Schelling, Hegel remain of considerable interest for cultural studies, sociology, theology, aesthetics and other areas of interest. In the domain of philosophy, the renaissance of innovative readings of German Idealism has taken scholarly debates beyond merely antiquarian perspectives. This renaissance has been a major factor of current efforts to bridge the gap between so-called “analytic” and so-called “continental” philosophy. The volume provides a selection of well-chosen examples of readings that contribute to systematic treatments of philosophical problems. It contains (among others) contributions by Markus Gabriel, Robert Pippin, Anders Moe Rasmussen, Sebastian Rödl.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 4aDeutscher Idealismus. 4aFichte, Johann Gottlieb. 4aGerman Idealism. 4aHegel, Georg Wilhelm Friedrich. 4aKant, Immanuel. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Idealism.2bisacsh1 aGabriel, Markus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRasmussen, Anders Moe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2017z9783110548228oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831104975190 cprintz978311050028840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311049861540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110498615423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110498615.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_D